My grandfather always referred to himself as a Portagee. I was suprised to learn some people have a
big issue with this. He grew up a farmer  and truck driver in Atwater, CA, then moved to Concord. CA and became real estate agent and broker. I was at a Holy Ghost in Hayward when this came up, so I wonder if it is a regional thing. Is it class related?  Anyone else have an opinion.

A family friend,who grew up in Red Bluff, CA,  Azorean and Mexican, like me, also called himself  Portagee as a simple description, without derision. He retired as a chief legal consul for the State of California, so a class based reaction doesn't seem likley

Eric Edgar

