My dad grew up on a farm on the central California coast (Orcutt, which is near Santa Maria), and I remember him often using the term &quot;Portagee&quot; when referring to people of Portuguese descent, including himself.  I can also recall his sisters using the word in the same manner.  There wasn't any negative connotation or stigma attached.  I've read that &quot;Portagee&quot; was used during the late 19th and early 20th centuries, particularly in California and other western states, to refer to Portuguese immigrants and did indeed have a negative inference.  It seems that over time the word has lost its sting and is now widely used in &quot;polite company&quot; as a general descriptive term.

Greg Lima
Washington State

