Kim,

I'm glad you brought it up. I'm not offended. I was very surprised to find out it's insulting, as every family member and friend of Azorean origin used it casually my whole life. The term seemed to get exposure through the writings of California authors like John Steinbeck and Jack London. I remember a Jack London story, I forget which one , where he goes on a racist tear about &quot; the Portagees&quot; in San Leandro. He couldn't stand it that they would use there front yards  for gardens, and or grow things along the roadside. Or the way they had their own clubs and churches. But what really irked him was that they would come over stay with relatives , work hard, lease some farm land, then buy some of their own, and a house , then a business.  Like it's a bad thing!

